== Zena
CMS based on Ruby on Rails, (c) Gaspard Bucher, teti.ch 2007, licenced under MIT

== Creating the database
You need to set collation and charset to utf8 when creating the database. Example :
# create database zena DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_general_ci;

== Migrating the database (setup)
Once config/database.yml is properly set, run the following command
# rake bricks:migrate
# rake bricks:init BRICK=zena

== Loading new languages
This is done through the web

dependencies:

rmagick, redcloth, syntax, markaby